    "science_concerns": {
      "type": "bloomli-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "con_1": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Nutrient gaps — filling the daily deficit",
            "answer": "<p>Hair follicles are among the fastest-dividing cells in the body with some of the highest nutritional demands of any tissue. When diet, absorption, or consistency is off, the follicle is one of the first places it shows — through increased shedding, slower growth, or reduced density over time.</p><p><strong>How Bloomli addresses it:</strong> Both formulas target the micronutrients most commonly depleted in women and most directly linked to hair health: biotin, zinc, and collagen-building amino acids. Consistent daily use helps maintain the steady follicle nourishment each growth cycle depends on.</p>",
            "open_by_default": true
          }
        },
        "con_2": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "DHT sensitivity — follicle-level support",
            "answer": "<p>Dihydrotestosterone (DHT) is a hormone that can progressively miniaturise hair follicles over time, gradually reducing strand diameter and density. DHT sensitivity has a genetic component, but the follicle environment — and how well it resists miniaturisation — can be influenced through supplementation.</p><p><strong>How Bloomli addresses it:</strong> Saw palmetto extract is included in both Bloomli formulas as a plant-based DHT balancer. Research suggests it may support a healthier follicle environment by modulating DHT activity at the scalp level, particularly with consistent long-term use.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        },
        "con_3": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Stress shedding — the cortisol-hair connection",
            "answer": "<p>Elevated cortisol can push hair follicles prematurely into the resting and shedding phase (telogen effluvium). The effect is often delayed — increased shedding typically appears 2–4 months after a stressful period, which is why many women feel like they're losing more hair without an obvious current cause.</p><p><strong>How Bloomli addresses it:</strong> Ashwagandha is included in both Bloomli formulas for its evidence-backed role in cortisol regulation. It supports the kind of stress resilience that may reduce the impact of high-cortisol periods on the hair cycle — without sedation or side effects at normal supplement doses.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        },
        "con_4": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Strand weakness — structural integrity from within",
            "answer": "<p>When hair feels brittle, breaks easily, or lacks shine, it often points to gaps in the structural proteins that make up the strand — particularly collagen and keratin. Topical treatments reach the surface. Nutritional gaps work from within, at every follicle.</p><p><strong>How Bloomli addresses it:</strong> Marine collagen peptides provide the amino acid precursors for keratin synthesis. Biotin supports the metabolic pathways involved in hair protein production. Together they address strand integrity at the source, not just the surface.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        },
        "con_5": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Scalp environment — the foundation of healthy growth",
            "answer": "<p>A healthy scalp is the foundation of healthy hair. Excess sebum, dryness, and microbiome imbalance can all affect how follicles perform over time. The scalp is skin — and it responds to the same nutritional and environmental factors as the rest of the body.</p><p><strong>How Bloomli addresses it:</strong> Zinc supports sebum regulation and follicle repair at the scalp level. The full Bloomli inside-out ritual — supplements plus topical scalp care — addresses both the internal and external dimensions of scalp health together.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": ["con_1", "con_2", "con_3", "con_4", "con_5"],
      "settings": {
        "heading": "What's happening beneath the surface.",
        "intro": "<p>Most visible hair changes have an internal cause that starts before you notice anything in the mirror. Expand each to understand the biology — and how Bloomli addresses it at the source.</p>",
        "show_placeholder": false,
        "image_position": "right",
