    "science_principles": {
      "type": "multicolumn",
      "blocks": {
        "pri_1": {
          "type": "column",
          "settings": {
            "title": "01. Published human data",
            "text": "<p>We prefer ingredients supported by peer-reviewed human trials. Animal studies and in-vitro research can inform hypotheses — but the closer the evidence is to a real person taking a supplement daily, the more weight it carries in our formulation decisions.</p>"
          }
        },
        "pri_2": {
          "type": "column",
          "settings": {
            "title": "02. Clinically meaningful doses",
            "text": "<p>Doses in Bloomli formulas are set to match the amounts used in clinical research. We don't use token amounts that look good on a Supplement Facts panel but deliver no meaningful physiological effect. This is what 'clinically dosed' actually means.</p>"
          }
        },
        "pri_3": {
          "type": "column",
          "settings": {
            "title": "03. A clear role in every formula",
            "text": "<p>Every active ingredient has a specific, explainable purpose. If we can't clearly describe what an ingredient does — in plain language, without jargon — it doesn't belong in the formula. No fillers added to extend the ingredient list.</p>"
          }
        },
        "pri_4": {
          "type": "column",
          "settings": {
            "title": "04. Honest claim language",
            "text": "<p>Bloomli supplements are routine wellness products, not medical treatments. We communicate benefits clearly without overpromising. You'll never see language implying these products diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease — because they don't, and saying otherwise would be misleading.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": ["pri_1", "pri_2", "pri_3", "pri_4"],
      "settings": {
        "title": "The four things we won't compromise on.",
        "heading_size": "h1",
        "image_width": "full",
