    "science_faq": {
      "type": "bloomli-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_1": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How long does it take to see results?",
            "answer": "<p>Hair grows approximately half an inch per month, and each follicle follows its own independent growth cycle. Most users notice reduced daily shedding and improved scalp comfort within 3–5 weeks of consistent use. Visible density and thickness changes typically emerge between months 2 and 4. Full results — where strands feel markedly thicker and stronger — generally consolidate around months 5 to 6. Results vary, and consistency is the primary variable in the outcome.</p>",
            "open_by_default": true
          }
        },
        "faq_2": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What does 'third-party tested' actually mean?",
            "answer": "<p>It means an independent laboratory — one not affiliated with Bloomli or our manufacturer — tests each batch against the product label. They verify potency (does the product contain what the label says, at the dose listed?), purity (is it free from heavy metals, microbial contamination, and adulterants?), and product integrity. A Certificate of Analysis (COA) is produced for every batch. This is the standard that separates credible supplement brands from those relying on self-reported quality claims.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        },
        "faq_3": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is the difference between the gummies and the capsules?",
            "answer": "<p>Both formulas share the core actives: biotin, zinc, saw palmetto, and ashwagandha. The differences reflect what each format makes possible. The gummies include marine collagen peptides and are pectin-based (vegan, gelatin-free, 2g sugar per serving). The capsule formula includes bamboo silica and a more concentrated botanical herbal blend — delivering actives at doses that are difficult to achieve in gummy format without compromising taste or texture. Both are third-party tested to the same standard.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        },
        "faq_4": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Why is the biotin dose 6,000 MCG?",
            "answer": "<p>6,000 MCG (6 mg) is the dose used in multiple peer-reviewed clinical studies on biotin and hair outcomes in adults. Below roughly 2,500–5,000 MCG, most human research doesn't demonstrate meaningful results for hair support. We dose at 6,000 MCG so the formula operates in the range where the clinical evidence actually lives. The RDI for biotin is much lower, but RDI figures are designed for prevention of deficiency — not for therapeutic or cosmetic supplementation. Biotin has an established safety profile at this dose, and excess is excreted renally.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        },
        "faq_5": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What does saw palmetto do for hair?",
            "answer": "<p>Saw palmetto is a botanical extract studied for its role in inhibiting 5-alpha-reductase — the enzyme that converts testosterone into DHT. DHT (dihydrotestosterone) is the hormone most associated with follicle miniaturisation and androgenetic hair thinning. By modulating DHT activity at the scalp level, saw palmetto may help support a more favourable follicle environment, particularly for those with hormonal hair concerns. It's included in both Bloomli formulas as a standardised extract to ensure consistent potency batch to batch.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        },
        "faq_6": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Are Bloomli supplements a medical treatment?",
            "answer": "<p>No. Bloomli supplements are routine wellness products and are not intended to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease. These statements have not been evaluated by the Food and Drug Administration. If you are experiencing significant or sudden hair loss or any medical symptoms that concern you, we recommend consulting a qualified healthcare provider. Supplements can support a healthy routine — they are not a substitute for medical care when that's what's needed.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        },
        "faq_7": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can I take Bloomli alongside medications or other supplements?",
            "answer": "<p>The Bloomli formulas are built around nutrients with well-established safety profiles. That said, if you take prescription medications, are pregnant, nursing, trying to conceive, or have an existing medical condition, we recommend checking with your doctor or registered dietitian before adding any supplement to your routine. This is standard advice for supplementation generally — not a flag specific to Bloomli.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        }
